SIMPLE: imitable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imitable
<hw>Im"i*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imitabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>imitable</ets>. See
<er>Imitate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being imitated or
copied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The characters of man placed in lower stations of life are more
usefull, as being <qex>imitable</qex> by great numbers.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Worthy of imitation; <as>as, <ex>imitable</ex>
character or qualities</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imitableness</ent>⟦br⟧
